OL,5, The gambling industry is targeting     
OL,6, adverts at players of Fantasy Premier  
OL,7, League, an online football game that is
OL,8, open to children, the BBC has found.   
OL,10,FBetting firms are increasingly         
OL,11,Fsponsoring websites that are associated
OL,12,Fwith the popular game, known as FPL.   
OL,14,FWe found gambling ads and promotions on
OL,15,Fsome of the biggest FPL-related        
OL,16,Fpodcasts and social media feeds.       
OL,18,FAn MP who chairs a group on gambling   
OL,19,Fsaid the industry was trying to        
OL,20,F"infiltrate" sites used by children.   
